This is  in agreement with the interpretation of the low energy limit  of
this lattice model with a  symplectic fermion theory, as was proposed
in. In the latter paper, this identification was made
by using the fact that the hamiltonian is the anisotropic limit of a
vertex model which can be reinterpreted as a loop model, and thus as a
model of classical  spins in two dimensions, similar to the
one used in the analysis of the usual  model. It was then argued
that the integrable hamiltonian lies in the broken symmetry Goldstone
phase,
and that the low energy limit is 
the weak coupling limit of the supersphere sigma model,
whose target space is  (the equivalent of
