 In fact, one can check that
the thermodynamics of the spin chain, in this limit, coincides with
the thermodynamics of the field theory for the supersphere sigma model
discussed in: the introduction of heterogeneities
provides thus a regularization of this field theory. 

As always - and this can be related to  the 
Nielsen-Ninomiya theorem -  the massive degrees of freedom
near vanishing bare rapidity in the model with heterogenities are completed by massless degrees of freedom at large bare rapidities 
(edges of the Brillouin zone). These are the same massless modes that would be 
present in the homogeneous chain obtained by letting . The dynamics of these
massless modes decouples entirely from the dynamics of the massive ones, 
and one can identify the associated CFT with the weak coupling limit of the 
supersphere sigma model, that is, the symplectic fermion theory. 






